Detailed Description

An implementation of a "stack".

Uses an Vector to keep track of the elements.

uint32 Stack::getElementAt (  uint32  i  )  const [inline]
 

Inspect element i (counted from the bottom) of the "stack".

Use this to inspect an element, but without removing it.

Note that this should maybe not be a method of a stack, however it is added anyway since it is useful in many applications.

Parameters:
i Index of the (counted from the bottom of the "stack").
Returns:
The i:th element from the bottom.
